  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The absence of colonoscopy is a clinical problem that can't be ignored. According to previous&#xD;
      studies, the absence rate for outpatient colonoscopy is between 4% and 29%. The aim of this&#xD;
      study is to determine the reasons for colonoscopy appointment cancellations among inpatients&#xD;
      and to identify the factors associated with colonoscopy nonattendance.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
